<br>
What about if I support my guild and my friends get hurt? Tell me that isn't disloyal.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
What makes a strong lasting guild is when it is made up of players with like-minded gaming philosophies.  Guild's that habitually KS, train, etc. tend to recruit/guild players who KS, train, etc., and are unlikely to attract the kind of members that vehemently oppose such actions.<br>
<br>
If you are truely uncomfortable with the decisions your guild is making - you should leave that guild.  Chances are, the people you are friends with in your guild, are friends of yours for a reason, and probably feel similarly.  If your guild leader's are leading your guild down a path of destruction that you feel is not where you want to be in the game, leave. <br>
<br>
If it is merely a certain faction of your guild that is causing you to feel moral dilemnas, and your guild officers/leaders are either supporting this or unwilling to confront the problem guildmates, then you should leave the guild.<br>
<br>
This IS a game.  And no guild is binding.  You may take some heat for doing what you feel is right - but that's the price one pay's for resisting peer pressure.  Chances are you'll be happier staying true to yourself.<br>
<br>
 <p>Sirensa the Vicar<br>
Hoss<br>
Druzzil Ro

