<br>
I have a lot of problems with leaders doing things I do not like. But as Aanadien said authority is huge. That book shows it. You think you would stop someone from getting hurt but fact is you don't really know, and odds are against you. Epiphany's example was a little harsh. Grey lines are harder. The rationalization of it being just a game is a good one. But use it wisely, you may find yourself saying &quot;I will go along with my guild since it is only a game.&quot;<br>
